<br>
So, since I would never buy a Hummer, it would be OK if I went out and stole it?<br>
<br>
Obviously physical vs intellectual property is a bit different, so...<br>
<br>
Or, since I would never buy Warcraft III it is OK if I just use pirated copies?<br>
<br>
Perhaps you don't understand the concept of Intellectual Property.  You pay them for the right to USE that stuff.  You never OWN the music you buy, you just have right to use it.<br>
<br>
So whether you were planning to buy the CD or not, you are reaping the benefits reserved for the paying customers.<br>
<br>
Now, I am not saying I think the concept is flawless...  But until such time as we decide that Intellectual property doesn't exist, it is only fair to follow the rules. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fortuneoffear>Fortune of Fear</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/27/03 11:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm62.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=688.topic&index=54>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I hate the RIAA.  A lot.</span><hr size=1> People are reasonably honest, beleive it or not.<br>
